-Introduction

 My first missions on GunShip2000 were terrible; 2 missions and a long
 distance to go. Because I was alone, I was shot down very soon. And unless you
 got promoted to 2LT, you still had to fly alone, instead of doing a fast
 mission with 5 men. Somehow I discovered how to change the bits in the
 roster.dat file and changed it with a Filezapper. It was going very well,
 but I still wasn't satisfied (every time I promoted to BG, I had to load
 the zapper and change it AGAIN).
 Quite a while back (07/95), I 쳀inally decided to make an editor for this in AmosPro.
 After about 2 weeks, I started programming this editor in C, from scratch.
 It's now a lot faster, smaller, easier to use and there are more options.
 And hastalafiestababy here it is.

                     A GunShip2000 Roster File Editor

-Requirements

GSE requires an Amiga (surprise,surprise) with at least V37
and a Gunship2000 roster file. It also needs the asl.library, gadtools.library
and ReqTools.library

-Controls

With GSE you can change the Name, Unitname, ranking and the medals of the
active pilot.

You can control the editor by pressing a few buttons or selecting a menuitem.
When starting, there are only a few options available:
 * New
 * Load
 * About
 * Quit
      
When starting the default path/filename is dh1:gs2000/roster.dat and the default
save path/filename is RAM:dumroster.dat, but you can change this by editing the
ToolTypes. After loading all the options become available, including:
 *Save
 *Name
 *Unitname
 *Rank selecting
 *Medal sliders


