-ToolTypes

 GSE has as loading default 'DH1:GS2000/roster.dat' and as saving default
 'RAM:dumroster.dat'. This is done to ensure that the original file isn't
 overwritten. Better save it to ram:, change the original filename and
 copy the modified file from ram:. You can set your own setting by changing
 the TOOLTYPES. There are four tooltypes:
  LOADNAME  Set a path & filename for loading.
  SAVENAME  Set a path & filename for saving.
   You should ALWAYS give the path and filename.
   Ex: LOADNAME=DH1:GS2000/roster.dat
  AREA  Set the BackFill Area. You can choose from 0 - 2. TRY IT !!! (>8-))
  SCREENFONT Set to TRUE or something else. This is handy if your screenfont
  is larger than 8 or 9 (or crashes), so you don't have to set the prefs to a smaller one.

